# Component Development Guidelines

## shadcn/ui Component Usage

When using shadcn/ui components in this project:

1. **Check component availability**: If a component is not installed, add it first:
   ```bash
   npx shadcn@latest add button
   ```

2. **Import paths**: Always use the `@/` alias
   ```tsx
   import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
   import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
   ```

3. **Class merging**: Use the `cn()` utility from [lib/utils.ts](mdc:lib/utils.ts)
   ```tsx
   <Button className={cn("w-full", isActive && "bg-accent")}>
     Click me
   </Button>
   ```

4. **Color tokens**: Use semantic color variables
   ```tsx
   // Good ✓
   <div className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
   <div className="text-muted-foreground">
   
   // Avoid ✗
   <div className="bg-black text-white">
   <div className="text-gray-500">
   ```

## Component Structure

Organize components following this pattern:

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
import { type ComponentProps } from "react"

interface MyComponentProps extends ComponentProps<"div"> {
  // Add custom props here
}

export function MyComponent({ 
  className,
  children,
  ...props 
}: MyComponentProps) {
  return (
    <div className={cn("base-styles", className)} {...props}>
      {children}
    </div>
  )
}
```

